"v.使永存，使永记不忘 【英】 v. 使永存，使永记不忘( to make perpetual) 【记】 per(全部)＋pet(追求 )＋uate→永远追求→ 永存 【例】 Storytellers have perpetuated ancient tales and legends since early times. v. 使永存不朽; 使永记不忘 【记】per全部, pet追求, uate－永远追求－永垂不朽 【类】transient: vanish = constant: perpetuate短暂的是突然消失的特征 = 不变的是不朽的特征 【反】debunk(v 揭穿)－perpetuate to sham(永远的伪装) 【记】per 全部，穿过 + pet 宠物，宠爱的人，与宠爱的人永远在一起,永记不忘 perpetuate (v.)  1520s, a back-formation from perpetuation or else from Latin perpetuatus, past participle of perpetuare ""to make perpetual,"" from perpetuus (see perpetual). Related: Perpetuated; Perpetuating."
